Former Transet and Eskom CFO, Anoj Singh has been booted out of the South African Institute of Chartered Accountants. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Transnet and Eskom CFO, Anoj Singh, has been booted out of the South African Institute of Chartered Accountants (Saica).
Singh has been found guilty of 12 of the 18 charges against him. The charges relate to his conduct at Transnet and Eskom between 2012 and 2015. READ: Over 40 accounts linked to Gauteng PPE tenders frozen He was implicated in wrongdoing in Transnet's controversial procurement of over 1,000 locomotives for more than R38-billion in 2014. He stands accused of colluding with Regiments Capital, which is associated with the Gupta family. Singh has been ordered to pay a 50 percent contribution towards the costs incurred by Saica in respect of his disciplinary case.